    <text id="R13770743T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Confederate General John C. Breckinridge writes from Staunton to Colonel
                    McCausland concerning May, 1864, troop movements.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Col. MCCAUSLAND:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-05-18">May 18, 1864.</date>
                        <name type="place">STAUNTON,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>Your dispatch of yesterday received. Gen. Morgan was ordered to report to me the
                    day I left Dublin, and unless Gen. Jones is in command as senior officer in the
                    department. If so, communicate with and report to him. Have report this morning
                    that enemy is still in Monroe. I hope Jones, Morgan, and yourself will drive him
                    out, and that there will be concert of action. The moment you can be spared I
                    want you to join me. Bring the Forty-fifth Regt. to Hanover Junction or
                    elsewhere.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>JNO. C. BRECKINRIDGE,<lb/> Maj.-Gen.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
